sample_source_name_ch1: prostate biopsy from prostate cancer patient
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: RNA was prepared using the miRNeasy kit (Qiagen, Valencia, CA) following the manufacturer's recommendations. The protocol includes dhomogenization of prostate biopsy samples, and an on-column DNase digestion. RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop-1000 spectrophotometer and quality was monitored with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
sample_label_protocol_ch1: Cyanine-3 (Cy3) labeled cRNA was prepared from 250 ng RNA using Agilent's miRNA Complete Labeling according to the manufacturer's instructions. T4 RNA ligase and Cy-3-pCp were used for labeling the miRNA samples. The labeled RNA samples were purified by Micro Bio-Spin 6 column.
sample_data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 9.5.3 (Agilent) using default parameters for miRNA array to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal intensities.  The feature extraction files were imported to Agilent's Genespring program for data analysis. The quantile normalization and log2 transformation was applied to get the normalized data accross the 56 arrays.
sample_hyb_protocol: Cy3-labelled miRNA samples were hybridized in a reaction volume of 45 µl containing 1x Hi-PRM hybridization buffer and 1x GE blocking agent following the manufacturers instructions. The mixed samples were hybridized to Agilent Human miRNA Microarrays (G4112A) for 20 hours at 55°C in a rotating Agilent hybridization oven.  After hybridization, microarrays were washed 5 minute at room temperature with Gene Expression Wash Buffer 1 (Agilent) and 5 minute with 37°C GE Wash buffer 2 (Agilent), then d ...

RNA was quantified using a NanoDrop-1000 spectrophotometer and quality was monitored with the Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Santa Clara, CA).
sample_label_protocol_ch1: Cyanine-3 (Cy3) labeled cRNA was prepared from 250 ng RNA using Agilent's miRNA Complete Labeling according to the manufacturer's instructions. T4 RNA ligase and Cy-3-pCp were used for labeling the miRNA samples. The labeled RNA samples were purified by Micro Bio-Spin 6 column.
sample_data_processing: The scanned images were analyzed with Feature Extraction Software 9.5.3 (Agilent) using default parameters for miRNA array to obtain background subtracted and spatially detrended Processed Signal intensities.  The feature extraction files were imported to Agilent's Genespring program for data analysis. The quantile normalization and log2 transformation was applied to get the normalized data accross the 56 arrays.
tissue: patient matched normal tissue from EA
sample_hyb_protocol: Cy3-labelled miRNA samples were hybridized in a reaction volume of 45 µl containing 1x Hi-PRM hybridization buffer and 1x GE blocking agent following the manufacturers instructions. The mixed samples were hybridized to Agilent Human miRNA Microarrays (G4112A) for 20 hours at 55°C in a rotating Agilent hybridization oven.  After hybridization, microarrays were washed 5 minute at room temperature with Gene Expression Wash Buffer 1 (Agilent) and 5 minute with 37°C GE Wash buffer 2 (Agilent), then d ...

sample_source_name_ch1: prostate biopsy from prostate cancer patient
sample_extract_protocol_ch1: All RNA samples were purified by using Qiagen RNeasy micro kit (Qiagen). Samples were then treated with the RiobMinus, rRNA reduction kit (Invitrogen), cDNA synthesis and amplification was performed using the WT cDNA synthesis and amplification kit (Affymetrix).
sample_label_protocol_ch1: Samples were enzymatically fragmented and biotinylated using the WT Terminal Labeling Kit (Affymetrix)
sample_data_processing: Data were processed using Partek Genomics Suite software. Quantile normalization and GC-RMA background correction were applied to probe intensities, gene level expression were summarized from the corrected/normalized intensities. Only core probe sets were used for data analysis., HuEx-1_0-st-v2.r2.pgf
sample_hyb_protocol: Samples were hybridized using Affymetrix hybridization kit materials. Heat cocktails at 99° for 5 minutes, then 42° for 5 minutes centrifuge at max speed for 1 minute. Transfer 200μl of hyb solution to each array, then tape holes and parafilm. Hybridize 16 hours at 45° at 60rpm. Fluidics washing is FS450_0001
